<Class name="CM_EDIBillOfLadingTI" id="29567b1c-6123-40ea-8e04-7414cc085849">
    <superclass name="CM_EDITrackedItem"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>Implemented 7.6.3 for X12 309 U.S. Customs Manifest file

Cargo is transmitted from U.S. Customs grouped by bill of lading.
JMTerminal receives these files, builds an EDI data Bill of Lading file and then
creates what it expects to be a set of tracked items (from the VID record of the EDI file).
Those tracked items in turn will have a set of remarks (from the N10 record of the EDI) that will be
stored against the VID/EDITrackedItem.
</text>
    <DbClassMap file="edi"/>
    <PrimAttribute name="marks" id="0bc88aa0-a600-45f5-b1f1-9ef587f708b5">
        <length>49</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>Currently set to length 48 as that is what the data field length in the 309 file is.
Not sure where it's going to be used yet but each VID record (container/equipment)
uses the first N10 record to indicate the quantity, the marks and summary of the cargo
in the VID.

</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="quantityOnCargo" id="a1d50c3f-f7ed-42e5-bb98-cfaae89ad859">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <CompAttribute name="remarksArray" id="463ca446-717f-493d-935f-d9398d99e34f">
        <type name="StringArray"/>
    </CompAttribute>
    <JadeMethod name="assignValueSpecial" id="415a7083-b7f0-4119-b1ce-1d0fd699dac7">
        <updating/>
        <source>assignValueSpecial(_propName: String; _processedValue: String; _xlationOperator: CM_Operator): Boolean updating;
//
//06 August 2018	jlgrs1	TFS 40086 JMT Not all EDI TrackedItem stringArray are exposed to the EDI JMT Internal
//
vars
	strArray : StringArray;
begin
	if _propName = CM_EDIBillOfLadingTI::remarksArray.name then
		self.remarksArray.clear();
		strArray := _processedValue.getTokens();
		if strArray &lt;&gt; null and 
		   not strArray.isEmpty then
			strArray.copy(self.remarksArray);
		endif;	
		return true;
	else
		return inheritMethod(_propName, _processedValue, _xlationOperator);
	endif;
epilog
	delete strArray;
end;</source>
        <Parameter name="_propName" type="String"/>
        <Parameter name="_processedValue" type="String"/>
        <Parameter name="_xlationOperator" type="CM_Operator"/>
        <ReturnType type="Boolean"/>
    </JadeMethod>
    <JadeMethod name="canUserSet" id="4c1fd1ff-e977-47e0-a1c2-b3c7d02f9228">
        <source>canUserSet(_propName: String): Boolean;
//
// 30 Jun 2014	cnwrs1	Par 34702 - Add support for JMT XML
//
//06 August 2018	jlgrs1	TFS 40086 JMT Not all EDI TrackedItem stringArray are exposed to the EDI JMT Internal
vars

begin
	if _propName = CM_EDIBillOfLadingTI::remarksArray.name then
		return true;
	else
		return inheritMethod(_propName);
	endif;
end;
</source>
        <Parameter name="_propName" type="String"/>
        <ReturnType type="Boolean"/>
    </JadeMethod>
    <JadeMethod name="getMyTIDisplayDefName" id="55e5d1fc-ced8-4ca5-bcc9-c7b03e4928f8">
        <source>getMyTIDisplayDefName(): String;

vars

begin
	return ETDef_EDITIUSCustManifest;
end;
</source>
        <ReturnType type="String"/>
    </JadeMethod>
    <JadeMethod name="setForUpdate" id="9f932fa3-2b07-450b-838c-1a6f1b748409">
        <updating/>
        <source>setForUpdate(_proxyEDITI: SelfType) updating;
//
//03 August 2018	jlgrs1	Initial creation
//
vars

begin
	inheritMethod(_proxyEDITI);
	self.marks := _proxyEDITI.marks;
	self.quantityOnCargo := _proxyEDITI.quantityOnCargo;
	self.remarksArray.clear;
	_proxyEDITI.remarksArray.copy(self.remarksArray);
epilog

end;</source>
        <Parameter name="_proxyEDITI" type="SelfType"/>
    </JadeMethod>
</Class>
